rComments: Sean is the Leonardo da Vinci of teaching. A true master of the art who possesses a rare teaching talent. Easily one of the best professors I have ever had. He cares about his students and gives incredible lectures. Be prepared to work lots though. ECE422 was not a walk in the park.

He is great...Clear notes..Everything was smooth crystal clear..(Take it from me..I attended both sections..ECE320-01 and 02...these two profs are absolutely fantastic..I just left this rating thing for one for prof.Eleftheriades...as well.) anyway Great prof...
Awesome Professor! Extremely helpful during office hours / even the morning before the final exam! Good teaching style. Gives hard tests but fair to everyone.
Great Prof, always helpful! Held SEVERAL review sessions!

He's a new professor in UofT - started in Sep. 2006. He is exceptionally great professor: bright, crystal clear, concise, funny, very well prepared, extremely attentive to students' questions. He's arguably one of the best professors I had.
